Saudi Arabiaâ€™s King Abdullah bin
Abdulaziz will travel to the U.S. tomorrow for further medical
checks and to receive treatment, the official Saudi Press Agency
announced today.  Doctors advised the 86-year-old monarch to rest after
medical examinations showed a slipped disc had caused a blood
clot that put pressure on his nerves, SPA said yesterday.  The king appeared on state television during the Eid al-
Adha Islamic feast receiving senior officials. He told his
guests that he regretted not being able to stand up to shake
